line_2: She must not tire her lily hands,

line_1: In vain she pines, the holy Faith withstands,
line_2: What Nature dictates and what God commands:

line_1: His weaker Trust the stubborn Weight withstands,
line_2: And backward sinks him down to lowest Sands.
The encroaching tide, that drowns her lessening lands,

line_1: Now faintly drop, no obstacle withstands
line_2: Proud of the Reins, which from his trembling hands
